        <item>
          <title>Kennard scores 27, LeBron leads Lakers to surprising 107-98 win over Rockets in playoff opener</title>
          <description><![CDATA[Luke Kennard scored a career playoff-high 27 points, LeBron James had 19 points and 13 assists, and the short-handed Los Angeles Lakers capitalized on Kevin Durant’s injury absence for a 107-98 victory over the Houston Rockets in the opener of their first-round playoff series.]]></description>
